<br>
When a melee procs a weapon, you don't see them casting a spell. I group with some of the highest end people on my server, as I am in the second best guild on my server. About half of them have weapons that proc in some way, be it Avatar, or Flame of the Efreeti, or Combust, or Careless Lightning.  I have -all- my spell information on in a little window to the side, so that I know who is casting what and when. Whenever they proc, you just see the message, except for a ranger using that fire proc buff, because that proc actually has a cast time and can be interrupted.<br>
<br>
Also, air and water pets stop (and complete their STUPID ANIMATION) when they are casting on a running mob. As I said before, -all- our pets cast exclusively, except the epic pet that procs and casts. This isn't an opinion, nor is it an assumption, it's a fact of the game.<br>
<br>
Testing statistics also isn't mysterious, nor is it all that difficult. Str effects damage, this can be parsed. Dex effects procs (which we now have weapons we can give to pets to make them proc), this can be parsed. Stamina gives hitpoints, but myself and others have come to the conclusion that it doesn't do anything to pets. This leads us to question whether dex/str/agi are doing anything either.  I personally don't know, but would love to find out. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:perpetua;font-size:x-small;">Turzem Setanta -- <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=474148">Arch Mage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.insidiousblood.net">Insidious Blood</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iwanthewicca>IwanTheWicca</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 127<br> <font color=#333333>(1/2/03 8:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=918.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet 8 item limit</span><hr size=1> We can determine this by using the Elemental Defender. As everyone knows, this item is automatically equipped in the secondary slot (thus hampering the pet's ability to dual weild)<br>
<br>
So, hand the pet as many items as you wish (8+) and see if ti equips the Elemental Defender. If the graphic does nto display, then the item is not equipped.<br>
<br>
if it does, this could mean that the pet will onyl equip the 8 most recently given items, but here's hoping that doesn't happen! <p>Majishia Vie &lt;Wyrd Angles&gt;<br>
