Repeat after me. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>PETS DO NOT PROC INNATELY</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> except epic.<br>
<br>
It's not exactly the same as traditional spell, more like an ability such as <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>bash/kick/FD</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> etc...<br>
<br>
It <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>casts</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> acted exactly as a spell except it's on a timer.<br>
Meaning it will cast in x seconds after the first cast. (as much as a war kicks after x seconds each time). Which seemed more like an ability to me.<br>
<br>
And I don't think it takes mana either, but i haven't tested that which is easy to try--duel a ENC see if you can mana tap a pet. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Basing the assumption on this means that every melee out there with proc weapons, plus about 80+% of all mobs in the game cast instead of proc. When a Rogue is wielding a proc'ing weapons, say a Stilleto Of Bloodclaw, you will see the message 'soandso begins to cast a spell', further when fighting LDC's, I often see them casting boil blood, but I know they proc due to the fact that their melee is not interrupted by the proc.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Not the same with pets. <br>
If you have seen sepic you should've known that. <br>
<br>
When epic procs, it doesn't give a pet_01 is casting a spell. <br>
Nor when the procing weapons proced. <br>
<br>
You can see the messages:<br>
&quot;mob_01 is hitted by shards of elemental power&quot; or <br>
&quot;mob_01 is hitted by flying debris&quot;<br>
but never a casting message before that.<br>
<br>
<br>
Only when it's casting its stun it has &quot;pet_01 is casting a spell&quot; message.<br>
